cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SP, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with sparse support recovery, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a data-driven approach using auto-encoder in deep learning, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses an application example in device activity detection for mMTC, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SP (Signal Processing).
